FSTYPE=zfs&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;sanity-benchmark test_bonnie also hit the same failure:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/82f29600-095b-11e3-ad8a-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/82f29600-095b-11e3-ad8a-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="62728" author="utopiabound" created="Mon, 22 Jul 2013 20:18:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I believe this is another zfs performance issue a la &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2887&quot; title=&quot;sanity-quota test_12a: slow due to ZFS VMs sharing single disk&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2887&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2887&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The completion times for this test when it passes on ZFS are in the range 1800-3400 which out-lairs on either side, so those that timeout are just running long and no a failure per se.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
